{"id":"math120-lineval-fg002wrd","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Functions and Graphs","subtopic":"Evaluating functions","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A cost function is C(x) = {m}x + {b} dollars, where x is the number of items produced. Find C({x_val}) and interpret the result.","params":{"m":{"type":"int","min":5,"max":30},"b":{"type":"int","min":200,"max":800},"x_val":{"type":"int","min":10,"max":40}},"answer_expr":"lineval","steps":["C({x_val}) = {m}({x_val}) + {b} = {m_times_x} + {b} = {answer_lineval}.","It costs ${answer_lineval} to produce {x_val} items."],"tags":["survey-calculus","functions","cost","interpretation"]}
